Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.35,0:00:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.26,0:00:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This month, we focus \Non how we can refine ourselves as Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.23,0:00:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by imitating Jehovah’s holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.56,0:00:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you sometimes say things you later regret
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.17,0:00:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—something unkind,\Nperhaps critical of others?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll learn from this dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.81,0:00:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,how to adjust\Nnot only what we say
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.98,0:00:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but also how we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.61,0:00:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re a young person,\Ndo you ever feel you’re in a fight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.52,0:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—a fight to please Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a fight to be joyful despite opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.89,0:00:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll enjoy our new music video.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.63,0:00:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of Jehovah’s people have suffered
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,disappointing spiritual setbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah lovingly wants\Npeople to return to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.47,0:00:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how he helped this man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.37,0:00:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,turn his life around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this and more
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.18,0:01:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on JW Broadcasting for October 2019!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.33,0:01:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say the words “holy” and “holiness,”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what comes to your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.04,0:01:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Many think of words like “clean” and “pure.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.88,0:01:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s change the question a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.31,0:01:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who comes to your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.72,0:01:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely, you think of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.42,0:01:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You might also picture\NJesus Christ and the holy angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.26,0:01:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you think of imperfect humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.93,0:01:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can humans be described as holy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.53,0:01:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.53,0:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We know this because humans\Nwere created in God’s image.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.53,0:02:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we can reflect godly qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as love, kindness, and self-control—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.21,0:02:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we can reflect holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.94,0:02:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How seriously should we take holiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no small matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the world around us\Nis increasing in badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Timothy 3:13 warns
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.52,0:02:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘wicked men\Nwould advance from bad to worse.’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.03,0:02:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Undoubtedly, before the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.33,0:02:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan’s efforts\Nto promote wickedness will intensify.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we must intensify our efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.74,0:02:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to be holy and reject all badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think are Satan’s primary targets?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.81,0:02:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.81,0:02:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He and the demons are\Nlike a pack of hungry lions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.75,0:02:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,looking to devour us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.99,0:02:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a publisher of the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.19,0:02:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is a privilege that Satan seeks to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.49,0:02:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a parent with children?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think Satan\Nwants you to become unclean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.40,0:03:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that devouring a family head
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.07,0:03:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,could weaken an entire family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.74,0:03:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan would love to devour\Nyou dear pioneers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.88,0:03:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ministerial servants, and elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you in the circuit work?\Na missionary? a Bethelite?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.32,0:03:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sacred privilege!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember, it also means\Nthat we have a big target on our back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.86,0:03:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan and the demons would love
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to penetrate our clean and holy position.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.67,0:03:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing so could impact\Nthe Kingdom work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or stumble others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can’t be complacent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.51,0:03:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We must intensify our efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to reject all badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.55,0:03:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, holiness is a vital topic!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.32,0:03:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end,\Nthe theme for this month’s program
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is “Perfecting Holiness in the Fear of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.53,0:04:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s based on 2 Corinthians 7:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin, we need to better understand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the Source of holiness, Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.67,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read the Bible, we see that holiness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is an important quality\Nthat Jehovah wants us to know about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible contains many verses
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that associate God’s name\Nwith the words “holy” and “holiness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your copy of the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.06,0:04:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to one example in Isaiah chapter 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll start at Isaiah 6:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now imagine that you’re the prophet Isaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.33,0:04:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who received a divine vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.94,0:04:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you have seen and heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verses 1 to 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the year that King Uzziah died,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.71,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“I saw Jehovah sitting\Non a lofty and elevated throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the skirts\Nof his robe filled the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Seraphs were standing above him;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“each had six wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.86,0:05:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Each covered his face with two\Nand covered his feet with two,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“and each of them would fly about with two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.03,0:05:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“And one called to the other:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.47,0:05:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Holy, holy, holy is Jehovah of armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole earth is filled with his glory.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah was likely filled with awe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.15,0:05:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 2 indicates that he saw seraphs,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit creatures evidently of very high rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.29,0:05:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we learn from their song?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.19,0:05:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Their repeating the word “holy” three times
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,teaches us that Jehovah\Nis holy to the superlative degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else is as holy as he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But what exactly is holiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.44,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to be holy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.61,0:06:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s dig deeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do so with a helpful tool found
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the revised {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t have\Nthe revised edition in your language,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll share the key point in just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.82,0:06:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the revised printed edition,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.02,0:06:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the glossary is located\Nseveral pages after Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.76,0:06:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and immediately after\Nthe “Bible Words Index.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The topics are arranged alphabetically.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So please find the entry\Nfor “Holy; Holiness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are using {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}JW Library®, 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,here are two ways to get to the glossary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the app, go to the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at the top of the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.78,0:06:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on the magnifying glass\Nto start a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then type in the word “holy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon you’ll see an entry from the glossary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.69,0:06:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tap on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way is to go to Publications
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.40,0:06:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then Books.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:07:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,From there you can open the glossary\Nand find the entry for “holy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.90,0:07:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.94,0:07:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“A quality possessed inherently by Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.55,0:07:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“a state of absolute\Nmoral purity and sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.35,0:07:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“When referring to humans, animals, things,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“places, time periods, and activities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.66,0:07:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“the original Hebrew word conveys the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“of separateness, exclusiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.03,0:07:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“or sanctification to the holy God;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“a state of being set aside\Nfor Jehovah’s service.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.30,0:07:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the Christian Greek Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“the words rendered ‘holy’ and ‘holiness’
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.24,0:07:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“likewise denote separation to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“The words are also used to refer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to purity in one’s personal conduct.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.35,0:07:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we’re reminded that Jehovah is pure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.09,0:07:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the absolute sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.09,0:08:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does it mean that holiness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is a quality that he possesses inherently?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s illustrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the words “human” and “imperfect.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, those two words naturally go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.48,0:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperfection is within all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.31,0:08:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and affects everything we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.85,0:08:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now consider another set of words
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that consistently go together:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah” and “holy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.36,0:08:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Holiness permeates Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t have to perfect\Nholiness like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.90,0:08:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything about him\Nis inherently clean,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.47,0:08:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,pure, and upright.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.17,0:08:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What a contrast\NJehovah’s holiness is to the world around us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.91,0:08:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, virtually everything
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.28,0:08:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about human society alienated from God
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is polluted in some way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,either by inherited imperfection\Nor by outright wickedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.62,0:09:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah\Nis completely removed from sinfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll never be polluted by badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.26,0:09:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll never turn corrupt,\Nimmoral, or abusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he’s absolutely holy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s completely reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that Jehovah is the ideal Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How encouraging and reassuring!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.58,0:09:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s holiness is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel about beautiful things?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.49,0:09:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you drawn to them or repelled by them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.49,0:09:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, look at these landscapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to spend time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see yourself walking here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.24,0:09:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,filling your lungs with clean, fresh air?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or how about drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.18,0:10:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,from a river of pure, crystal-clear water?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.42,0:10:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How we yearn to live in such conditions!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But have you ever wondered what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about these images that’s so appealing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply put, everything is pure and clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.23,0:10:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, if these same locations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.94,0:10:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,were filled with garbage, graffiti, and smog,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,would you still want to be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.84,0:10:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Pollution and filth are not attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.78,0:10:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re naturally drawn to beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty is associated with things\Nthat are clean, pure, and bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.23,0:10:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.26,0:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,wants us to view his holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditating on this aspect\Nof God’s personality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,draws us closer to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And though he hates all sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,his Word confirms that he doesn’t hate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.48,0:11:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this stirs within us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a desire to perfect holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now open to 2 Corinthians 7:1,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our theme scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Though Paul wrote this to one congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.50,0:11:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah preserved it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.80,0:11:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It says:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, since we have these promises,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.87,0:11:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“beloved ones, let us cleanse ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“of every defilement of flesh and spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,perfecting holiness in the fear of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.85,0:11:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The concluding part of the verse\Nserves as the basis for our theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.89,0:11:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to perfect something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.76,0:11:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,According to one dictionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.03,0:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to “perfect” means\N“to bring to a state of supreme excellence,”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:12:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to “rid of faults,” to “improve” or “refine.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, perhaps you enjoy a hobby
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.11,0:12:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,like drawing, taking photographs,\Nor playing an instrument.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.55,0:12:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If an expert in that field told you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that you should {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}perfec{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}t {\r} your talent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what would he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.59,0:12:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he’s confirming\Nthat you have some experience already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.29,0:12:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, he’s telling you:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“You have what it takes\Nto be even better in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.03,0:12:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see your potential!”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.60,0:12:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, perfecting a hobby takes time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.34,0:12:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is true of our holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The book\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Word Pictures in the New Testament{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}notes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that the word “perfecting”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.48,0:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Corinthians 7:1
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,means “not a sudden attainment\Nof complete holiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but a continuous process.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.69,0:12:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah, the expert in holiness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.96,0:13:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and our best Friend, is appealing to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, he’s saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.17,0:13:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I see your potential!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.57,0:13:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You have what it takes\Nto make progress in holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep working to perfect it!’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Does such an appeal touch your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.75,0:13:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We could ask ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.92,0:13:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Is there an area in my life\Nwhere I can refine my holiness?’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, consider the matter\Nof physical cleanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.76,0:13:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 8 of the book\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}How to Remain in God’s Love 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.70,0:13:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,discusses the need to glorify Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.77,0:13:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by keeping our body and clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.17,0:13:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,our home and surroundings,\Nand our place of worship clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.71,0:13:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Being physically clean\Nbenefits us and those around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,More important, it honors our Holy Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.59,0:14:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But our personal cleaning program\Nmust go below the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.59,0:14:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In our theme text, Jehovah urges us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.66,0:14:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to “cleanse ourselves\Nof every defilement of flesh and spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This involves every aspect of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.10,0:14:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, something we read in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.07,0:14:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or that we hear at a meeting may warn us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.84,0:14:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that our thoughts need further refinement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we detect\Na tendency toward materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or we realize that our precious time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is being consumed by social media,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.42,0:14:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,surfing the Internet, or playing video games.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.29,0:14:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,At Ephesians 4:23, 24, we’re urged
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.50,0:14:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to “continue to be made new\Nin [our] dominant mental attitude”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.87,0:14:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and to “put on the new personality.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.54,0:14:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So our challenge might be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.61,0:14:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a deeply ingrained,\Nnegative personality trait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister named Cristina admitted:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.38,0:15:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“I often find myself\Nlooking enviously at others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.48,0:15:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I compare what they have\Nwith what I don’t have.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, these are just a few examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And these may not be our weaknesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but the lesson is clear:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us need to keep examining ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And, brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.97,0:15:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when we identify a personal weakness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.41,0:15:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For illustration purposes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s use the example\Nof Cristina and her battle with envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.82,0:15:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-step program
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.15,0:15:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to change our dominant mental attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was published on page 11 of the June 2019
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.86,0:15:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,study edition of {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.30,0:15:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the first thing Cristina should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.67,0:15:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Step 1: She needs to talk to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,admitting that she recognizes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:15:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the need to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:16:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If she prays regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.08,0:16:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah\Nto “put within [her] a new spirit,”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.38,0:16:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our holy God will help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.05,0:16:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Step 2: She needs to meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to examine herself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mirror of God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, she might think deeply
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.86,0:16:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about the fact that “love is not jealous”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.40,0:16:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and “does not look for its own interests.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.63,0:16:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This would help Cristina to hate envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Step 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs to assess her relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.68,0:16:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose good association.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that negative gossip,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.35,0:16:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,either in person or online,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.98,0:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is shaping her thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, she’d be wise\Nto choose better association.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.66,0:16:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah’s blessing\Nupon Cristina’s personal efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will enable her to perfect holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.57,0:17:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These three steps can help us do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.37,0:17:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now review our key points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.71,0:17:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,First, wickedness\Nis going “from bad to worse,”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.51,0:17:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so we need to intensify\Nour efforts to be holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.52,0:17:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, since Jehovah\Nis the Source of holiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,everything about him\Nis clean, pure, and upright.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.89,0:17:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This beautiful quality draws us to him
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.26,0:17:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and moves us to be holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Third and most important,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.07,0:17:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah appeals to us
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.11,0:17:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to “cleanse ourselves\Nof every defilement of flesh and spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So may we accept Jehovah’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.61,0:17:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and work to perfect holiness in God’s fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.42,0:17:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as we strive to perfect holiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:17:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t look down on people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.86,0:17:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been molded by the world around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following experience from Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.50,0:18:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how a group of young men
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.37,0:18:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who had a rough start in life\Nwere drawn to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.97,0:18:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and what a courageous sister did\Nto reach their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Our parents loved us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.48,0:18:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but they did it in the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.62,0:18:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They would often turn violent,\Nso we learned that way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.49,0:18:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that ever since I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid of coming home one day\Nand not finding my parents together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.50,0:18:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as far back as I remember,\Nthey have always argued with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.44,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we grew up with those values\Nand those ways of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that led us to become\Na group that was known and feared 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the area\Nbecause of our violent, immoral lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.85,0:18:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that was devoted to drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.85,0:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We had no rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:19:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We were people\Nthat you should stay away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.93,0:19:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was one of those regular mornings\Nwhen we were home alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it became our hideout\N—the place we would meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We had skipped school,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and our parents didn’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.94,0:19:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was with Federico\Nand Raffaele when two sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,two of Jehovah’s Witnesses,\Nrang the doorbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.98,0:19:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had them come in,\Nso we could make fun of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a matter of fact, that’s what we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.65,0:19:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that Maria\Nand the sister that was with her
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.16,0:19:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,were two very sincere and genuine people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They showed courage\Nas they brought us the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.10,0:19:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised that they were so kind,\Ndespite that my tone of voice was mocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.97,0:19:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really appreciated their kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t let anything stop her,\Nnot even the way we looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:20:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really touched\Nby the conversation with Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought I would never see her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.59,0:20:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would ever come back to people like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria didn’t give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.43,0:20:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She came back with an older pioneer brother\Nwho wasn’t scared of us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.04,0:20:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and with courage started to preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I really started\Nto change my life and make progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.95,0:20:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, I started to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I\Nwas learning with all my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What surprised me was my mother’s reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.45,0:20:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She wasn’t happy at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She reacted really violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.43,0:20:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They thought that I was going mad
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.70,0:20:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—that I was being brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.00,0:20:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that they\Nwould do everything to remind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:21:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of the strong friendship that was between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So they would put pressure on me emotionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I did love them\Nand was close to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I made the drastic decision to tell them
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.62,0:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that from then on I would no longer\Nbe staying in their company.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.26,0:21:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This situation made me really intrigued.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.33,0:21:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I ended up studying with Francesco.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,His determination really made me think.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.84,0:21:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was obvious\Nthat the things he was telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.51,0:21:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,were actually real—it was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.78,0:21:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, the strength\Nit took to go forward with this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.68,0:21:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—his determination to leave his friends—\Nwas surely what made
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us seriously interested\Nin the message he was preaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.39,0:21:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I would blame it on the truth\Nbecause it was taking my friend away from me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.30,0:21:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—a friend with whom\NI used to do the things I liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.80,0:22:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, inside I knew that even though\NI told him he had gone mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.67,0:22:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that inside\Nthere must have been something powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.61,0:22:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was so convinced,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and we could all sense his conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I realized\Nthat there was really something there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.58,0:22:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To my surprise, one after the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all of my friends started studying the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.39,0:22:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As I studied,\NI realized that it was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.86,0:22:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be hatred\Nthat always motivated my choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.40,0:22:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I act according to love,\Nand this makes me feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.44,0:22:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can now say that thanks to Maria 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.54,0:22:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and Francesco,\NJehovah tried to draw me to Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.41,0:22:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it’s been a miracle from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.45,0:22:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth helped me cultivate the qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.85,0:22:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of peace and joy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.45,0:22:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—the personality that has made it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.45,0:22:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to have the family I never had.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.06,0:23:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest satisfaction I have in life\Nis to have a relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.26,0:23:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I see someone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.80,0:23:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like we used to be,\NI feel motivated to speak to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.64,0:23:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The patience that Maria showed\Nmotivates me to be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.11,0:23:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite our reputation,\NMaria did not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.05,0:23:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She showed us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that in Jehovah’s eyes,\Nno one is beyond recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.39,0:23:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.36,0:23:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Before they found the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.83,0:23:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those young men were, as they put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.60,0:23:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“people that you should stay away from.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.23,0:23:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you have hesitated to give a witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.84,0:23:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sister Maria didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.27,0:23:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice what our brother did\Nwhen he embraced the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.18,0:23:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He went to his friends\Nand broke off his association.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.41,0:23:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew he needed friends\Nwho shared his determination to serve God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.15,0:23:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So do we.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.42,0:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the wonderful results.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.22,0:24:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are now brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.79,0:24:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They cleansed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.03,0:24:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was\Nthe most meaningful transformation?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.40,0:24:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brother said it:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.40,0:24:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It used to be hatred\Nthat motivated my choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.87,0:24:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it’s love.’
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.51,0:24:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we’re new in the truth\Nor have served Jehovah for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.31,0:24:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we can perfect holiness\Nand move forward as spiritual people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.32,0:24:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that in our next segment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.55,0:24:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for how our brothers\Napplied good suggestions from {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.44,0:24:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The challenge of serving\Nin a foreign country can sometimes be that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.87,0:24:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you’ve made that move\Nand you’ve learned a foreign language,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.98,0:24:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you can feel like you’ve done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.01,0:24:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up by a Witness mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.01,0:25:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so I studied the Bible since I was small.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.78,0:25:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I had\NBible knowledge to some extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.32,0:25:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I have enjoyed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.29,0:25:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the traveling work for 18 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.16,0:25:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get older,\Ntrials that we never experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.96,0:25:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were young\Nhave come up one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.03,0:25:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After I got married and had children,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.20,0:25:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a hard time explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.10,0:25:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the backgrounds\Nof some Bible characters or Biblical history
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.44,0:25:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when I studied the Bible with my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.35,0:25:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I realized
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.35,0:25:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that I did not have enough Bible knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.95,0:25:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And another challenge can be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.89,0:25:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re dealing\Nwith a foreign culture in the territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.86,0:25:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but you also have\Nmany different cultures in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.73,0:25:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When I struggle\Nto fulfill various responsibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.76,0:25:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in a balanced way
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.30,0:25:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—things such as caring for aged parents\Nand our own health issues—
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.20,0:25:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be a source of stress
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.47,0:26:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and cause tension between my wife and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.44,0:26:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The study article\N“Move Forward as a Spiritual Person!”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.35,0:26:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in February 2018 was a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.78,0:26:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The expressions:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.85,0:26:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“Once we have\Nidentified areas for improvement,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.95,0:26:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to take positive steps”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.09,0:26:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and that “it is a life-and-death matter”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.43,0:26:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,really touched my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.76,0:26:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized\Nthat I needed to scrutinize my life seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.93,0:26:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and make improvements\Nfor my own future and that of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.14,0:26:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The article had a quote\Nfrom Brother Barr that said:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.07,0:26:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Many fail because they\Nare not diligent enough to grow mighty.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.28,0:26:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This made me think,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.78,0:26:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Am I mighty enough\Nto overcome any challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that might come up,\Ndifficulties with brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.59,0:26:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that pleases Jehovah?’
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.12,0:26:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To move ahead as a spiritual person,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.06,0:26:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I needed\Nto get Jehovah’s thinking on matters
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.13,0:26:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and really look at Bible principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.09,0:26:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means letting go of my pride;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.63,0:26:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it comes back,\Nletting go of it again
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.23,0:27:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and really making\NJehovah’s thoughts my own thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.10,0:27:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a bad tendency to try to do everything
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.14,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by myself and to not\Ndelegate things to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.45,0:27:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked myself,\N‘What decision will please Jehovah?’
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.89,0:27:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Make sure of the more important things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.69,0:27:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt the need to train
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.82,0:27:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,younger brothers in the congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.89,0:27:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I could delegate\Nresponsibilities to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.36,0:27:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The article encouraged us\Nto look to Bible principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.50,0:27:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And two that really helped me
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.70,0:27:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,were Proverbs 15:28 and Philippians 2:4
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.14,0:27:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because it helped me to think
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.54,0:27:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about what is in the person’s best interests
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.11,0:27:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,before I respond to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.72,0:27:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I took time when reading Bible accounts
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.05,0:27:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to meditate on how I would feel
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.19,0:27:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if I were one of those Bible characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.49,0:28:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can now explain things better\Nat my children’s study.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.03,0:28:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m very happy to see my children
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.34,0:28:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,truly enjoying Christian activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.17,0:28:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My son started doing “play meetings” for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.18,0:28:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter loves the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.68,0:28:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She talks to people willingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.81,0:28:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not because we as parents\Nare telling her to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.72,0:28:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to how it was when I was a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.75,0:28:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things are totally different now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.92,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that really makes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.56,0:28:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,By applying this principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.10,0:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can lighten my load
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.60,0:28:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and reduce my stress level.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.87,0:28:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, that helps me to maintain joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.07,0:28:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to strengthen our relationship as a couple,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.57,0:28:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I feel I’ve become
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.04,0:28:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,more approachable\Nto those in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.78,0:28:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Having the “mind of Christ”\Nhas helped me in my assignment 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.29,0:29:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s helped me to form\Nreally close friendships 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with the brothers and sisters\Nin my congregation, and that’s brought me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.82,0:29:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of joy in my service.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.96,0:29:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, when I don’t know\Nwhat to do (which often happens),
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.83,0:29:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have Jehovah’s principles to guide me,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.23,0:29:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and that makes me feel safe and secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.95,0:29:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Family heads, did you notice
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.69,0:29:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,how Yusuke took to heart\Nthe suggestion to analyze his life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.03,0:29:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and look for ways to improve?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.53,0:29:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He realized\Nthat while he had some Bible knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.80,0:29:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he needed to deepen it\Nthrough study and meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.30,0:29:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That made him\Na more effective teacher for his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.14,0:29:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jane was doing fine work\Nas a pioneer in a foreign land.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.51,0:29:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, ironically, she had difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.41,0:30:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with brothers and sisters\Nfrom different cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.22,0:30:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.22,0:30:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What stood in her way?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.22,0:30:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, ‘I had to let go of my pride.’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.46,0:30:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once she did,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s thoughts became her thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.43,0:30:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, like Yutaka Kimura,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.17,0:30:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re dealing\Nwith changing life circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we learn from his example?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.84,0:30:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He delegated responsibilities\Nand reordered his priorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.68,0:30:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That took humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.78,0:30:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The result?\NReduced stress and increased joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.78,0:30:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, honest self-examination
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.95,0:30:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,reveals the root cause\Nof something we need to adjust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.32,0:30:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that\Nin the following dramatization.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.01,0:31:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I embarrassed my wife tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.28,0:31:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew when it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.98,0:31:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t want to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.84,0:31:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew in my heart that Yoomi was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.21,0:31:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I had become unkind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.21,0:31:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There were lots of examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.82,0:31:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d complained about the way one brother\Nconducted meetings for field service.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.30,0:31:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was jealous
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.43,0:32:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of a ministerial servant\Nwho received new privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.62,0:32:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was pretty blunt
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.62,0:32:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,about how frustrated I got\Nwith Yoomi’s parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I’d gotten rid\Nof my old personality,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.04,0:32:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it still lurked inside of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.58,0:32:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of my friends\Nwere OK with and even encouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.08,0:32:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,these bad qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.05,0:32:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The change was so gradual
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.29,0:32:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that I didn’t even realize\Nhow far I’d fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.66,0:32:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think I need to do to change?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.93,0:33:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we search\Nfor “good for building up”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.76,0:33:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from the ONLINE LIBRARY?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.40,0:33:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.\NLet’s take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.51,0:33:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We considered Ephesians 4:29,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.84,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which says:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let a rotten word\Nnot come out of your mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.41,0:33:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“but only what is good\Nfor building up . . . ,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.75,0:33:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to impart what is beneficial\Nto the hearers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.19,0:33:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was struck by this powerful word picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.96,0:33:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Rotten words are as disgusting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.13,0:33:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as rotten food.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.14,0:33:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want the things\Ncoming out of my mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to disgust my wife or anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.14,0:33:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But to change,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.28,0:33:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.82,0:33:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I really try to think before I speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.32,0:34:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a goal to give someone
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.79,0:34:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,real commendation at every meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.07,0:34:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a goal for my conversations too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to keep them\Nwholesome, true, and kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.78,0:34:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing how speaking kindly to others
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.22,0:34:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,can make you feel so good inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.39,0:34:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn’t be surprised,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.69,0:34:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s just another way\Nof showing God’s love.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.00,0:34:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think I’ll ever forget\Nthat image of the rotten fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.50,0:34:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn’t that the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.01,0:34:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No one wants their words\Nand conversations to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.51,0:35:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to perfect holiness\Nwith clean conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.28,0:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we keep our speech\Nupbuilding and kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.35,0:35:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like our brother,\Nwe need to look within ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.22,0:35:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s causing us to say hurtful things?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.56,0:35:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He discovered\Nthe “old personality” still lurking inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.66,0:35:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and he realized that some of his friends
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.73,0:35:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,were actually\Nencouraging his critical attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.47,0:35:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But he did more than analyze himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.84,0:35:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He made a plan and set goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.38,0:35:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As his thinking changed, so did his speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.45,0:35:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That drew people to him,\Nand he felt good inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.39,0:35:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As that brother realized,\Nsometimes even without noticing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.39,0:35:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we could move backward spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.63,0:35:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to move forward, perfecting holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.43,0:35:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll next hear from a brother\Nwho took more than a step or two backward.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.30,0:36:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what helped him\Nregain his relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.08,0:36:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My first contact\Nwith the Witnesses was in my 20’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.29,0:36:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As my knowledge increased,\NI made drastic changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.53,0:36:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I quit smoking\Nand stopped swearing and using drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.50,0:36:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I also changed my violent behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.54,0:36:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I completely gave up martial arts,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I was baptized\Nas one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.51,0:36:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an amazing day\Nthat I will never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.05,0:36:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after my baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.29,0:36:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I became quite involved\Nin my work at the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.49,0:36:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The environment there\Nwas very immoral, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.16,0:36:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after several loving warnings
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.36,0:36:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from brothers in the congregation\Nadvising me to look for another job,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.07,0:37:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I chose not to follow their advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.40,0:37:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d worked there for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.40,0:37:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought, ‘I can handle it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.41,0:37:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.51,0:37:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My conscience became dull,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.85,0:37:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I committed\Na serious sin against Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.89,0:37:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When I left the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.09,0:37:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,several offers came my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.16,0:37:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a manager at a nightclub\Nthat was open until six in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.36,0:37:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a lot of parties,\Nand it was a lot of drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.07,0:37:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I also resumed martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.28,0:37:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I came in contact with serious criminals
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.78,0:37:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and gradually became friends\Nwith the most influential person
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.25,0:37:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the criminal underworld in Oslo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.92,0:37:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually,\NI was imprisoned for my violent behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.69,0:38:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A Christian movement\Nvisited the prison where I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.96,0:38:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of the inmates were invited\Nto an event where there would be cake served.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.60,0:38:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounded very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.87,0:38:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was tempted by a cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.47,0:38:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They also played music.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.74,0:38:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But after a while, \Nthey started speaking in tongues,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.05,0:38:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I felt very uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.65,0:38:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to be involved in that,\Nbut I couldn’t get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.45,0:38:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I was big and strong back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.96,0:38:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I physically couldn’t stand up from my chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.59,0:38:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve experienced a lot in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.16,0:38:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but at that moment,\NI was genuinely scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.06,0:38:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I cried out to Jehovah,\Nand immediately I was released,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.80,0:38:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was able to get up and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.81,0:38:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This big man was now\Nin a fetal position, crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.81,0:38:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I called my wife\Nand asked her to bring me a Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.68,0:38:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and some literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:39:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to start studying again\Nand draw close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.79,0:39:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest challenge was prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.76,0:39:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—to start communicating with Jehovah again\Nafter being so far away from him,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.80,0:39:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,doing all these bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.80,0:39:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it was a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.14,0:39:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One scripture I especially remember 
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.14,0:39:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is Isaiah 1:18, where He says:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.95,0:39:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come, now,\Nand let us set matters straight between us.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.99,0:39:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That touched me deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.32,0:39:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He also says\Nthat if ‘your sins are red like scarlet,’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.33,0:39:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will make them “white as snow.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.00,0:39:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like he separated the darkness\Nand stretched out his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.20,0:39:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and pulled me out,\Nback into the light again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.15,0:40:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months after I was reinstated,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.12,0:40:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,my wife decided to dedicate her life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.19,0:40:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah and was baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.09,0:40:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She has been a huge support during my return.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.43,0:40:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very nervous at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.40,0:40:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I entered the Kingdom Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.04,0:40:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that feeling just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.60,0:40:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s spirit is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.87,0:40:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the brothers and sisters\Nacted toward each other
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.78,0:40:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,was such a contrast to my former lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.52,0:40:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel deeply blessed by Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.96,0:40:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you make mistakes once in a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.93,0:40:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I feel confident\Nthat Jehovah is merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:40:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At his lowest point, Petter said
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.87,0:41:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he felt ‘so far away from Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.44,0:41:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can relate\Nto his situation in some way,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.11,0:41:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,be assured that you too\Ncan “set matters straight.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.75,0:41:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can experience what Petter did
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.49,0:41:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah helped him\Nout of the darkness into the light again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.39,0:41:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Jehovah is saying to you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.10,0:41:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and to all of us: ‘I see your potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.27,0:41:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have what it takes.’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.00,0:41:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, some of the greatest challenges\Nare faced by our young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.71,0:41:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s music video\Nwas made especially for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.35,0:41:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s entitled\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}“Fight the Fine Fight of the Faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.97,0:42:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days I feel I’ve had enough.\NThe war in my mind can get so tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.25,0:42:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s days I feel there’s no way out.\NIn a flood of tears, I’m sinking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.76,0:42:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In my despair, he sees me through.\NWhen I am crushed, I know just what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.24,0:42:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I need his words of truth.\NI can hear Jehovah saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.61,0:42:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NAnd I will wipe out ev’ry tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.59,0:43:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NThe new world is in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.86,0:43:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just keep on holding tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.53,0:43:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll help you win this fight—\NFight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.21,0:43:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll help you win this fight.’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.65,0:43:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading his Word\Ngives me the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.05,0:43:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When storms in life come,\Nhe’s my strong Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.83,0:43:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In my despair, he pulls me through.\NWhen I am down, I know just what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.34,0:43:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I need his words of truth.\NI can hear Jehovah saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.41,0:44:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NAnd I will wipe out ev’ry tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.92,0:44:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NThe new world is in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.30,0:44:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just keep on holding tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.70,0:44:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll help you win this fight—\NFight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.64,0:44:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll help you win this fight.\NI’ll help you win this fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.15,0:44:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll help you win this fight.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.50,0:44:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll help you win this fight,\NHelp you win this fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.84,0:44:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Help you win this fight.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.92,0:45:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NAnd I will wipe out ev’ry tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.83,0:45:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just a little while longer,\NThe new world is in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.27,0:45:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep on holding tight.\NI’ll help you win this fight.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.48,0:45:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful song\Nand a beautiful reminder!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.19,0:45:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does help us\Nto win our “fight of the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.42,0:45:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In what ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.43,0:45:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw in the video, he helps us
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.69,0:45:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,through our family and fellow worshippers,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.20,0:45:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,through the ministry,\Nand through his Word, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.30,0:45:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Preserving God’s Word and his personal name
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.74,0:46:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,has been a fierce fight over many centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.01,0:46:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—a fight that’s being won.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.31,0:46:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the subject of the Bible Museum\Nat world headquarters in Warwick, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.25,0:46:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take a brief tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.02,0:46:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible is a modern-day treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.29,0:46:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It reveals the satisfying truth about God,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.49,0:46:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,life, and our hope for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.40,0:46:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s more,\Nit contains another priceless treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.67,0:46:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—God’s personal name, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.90,0:46:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How Jehovah preserved his name\Nin the Holy Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.68,0:46:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,against all attempts to remove it,\Nis a fascinating story.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.45,0:46:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s told here in the Bible Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.35,0:46:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,at world headquarters in Warwick.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.09,0:46:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take the tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.32,0:46:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At the museum’s entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.66,0:46:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the divine name is shown in various languages
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.09,0:46:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a total of 7,216 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.76,0:46:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how many times it appears
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.97,0:47:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the New World Translation\Nof the Holy Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.47,0:47:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah always made his name known,\Neven to the very first humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.14,0:47:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When Cain was born,\NEve declared:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.05,0:47:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have produced a male child
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.52,0:47:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.22,0:47:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,After that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.35,0:47:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,people knew and used God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.69,0:47:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The oldest example\Nof the divine name in Hebrew letters
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.36,0:47:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is on the Moabite Stone\Nfrom the ninth century B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.37,0:47:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Moabite King Mesha\Nboasted against Israel:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.50,0:47:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“I took from it the vessels of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.97,0:47:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and offered them before Chemosh.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.01,0:47:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s also evidence that in ancient times
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.65,0:47:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s name was used in everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.42,0:47:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This silver scroll\Nfrom the seventh century B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.25,0:47:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is the earliest known inscription
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.76,0:47:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of a Bible text containing God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.93,0:48:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.26,0:48:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“May Jehovah bless you and keep you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.73,0:48:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah make his face to shine on you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.94,0:48:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Most important, God’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.67,0:48:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was in ancient copies of the Bible text.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.57,0:48:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Fouad Papyrus
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.94,0:48:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from the first century B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.71,0:48:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fragment of the Greek Septuagint,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.72,0:48:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the first known translation
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.72,0:48:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Hebrew Scriptures into Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.29,0:48:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s Deuteronomy 32:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.89,0:48:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I will declare the name of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.36,0:48:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the text is in Greek,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.53,0:48:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the divine name is written in Hebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.57,0:48:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Greek-speaking Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.57,0:48:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jesus’ day used the Septuagint.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.74,0:48:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Jesus read and taught\Nfrom the Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.48,0:48:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,people heard him use the divine name.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.38,0:48:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, though,\Nby the third century C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.15,0:49:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s name was removed\Nfrom the Septuagint
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.45,0:49:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and replaced with the title “Lord.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.66,0:49:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.36,0:49:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the Vatican Codex
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.46,0:49:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from the fourth century C.E.\Nincludes the text
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.13,0:49:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Greek Septuagint\Nbut omits God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.00,0:49:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Deuteronomy 32:3 here reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.14,0:49:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I will declare the name of the LORD.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.17,0:49:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.84,0:49:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn’t allow his name to be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.95,0:49:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was never removed\Nfrom Hebrew copies of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.12,0:49:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Aleppo Codex
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.12,0:49:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was copied by Jewish scribes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.15,0:49:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,around the year 930 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.36,0:49:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The same verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.13,0:49:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Deuteronomy 32:3, says in Hebrew:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.63,0:49:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I will declare the name of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.10,0:49:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Still,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.10,0:49:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for centuries, most people didn’t have
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.30,0:49:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a Bible in their own language,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.64,0:49:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,nor one that contained God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.44,0:49:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Latin Vulgate,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.45,0:50:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,translated around 405 C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.48,0:50:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,omitted the divine name.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.52,0:50:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It became the official translation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.25,0:50:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Catholic Church for over 1,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.49,0:50:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But a new technology triggered events
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.63,0:50:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that would soon make\Nthe Bible widely available
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.37,0:50:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and in fresh translations
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.37,0:50:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that returned God’s name\Nto its rightful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.84,0:50:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,About 1453, \NJohannes Gutenberg
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.34,0:50:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,produced an important edition\Nof the Latin Vulgate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.14,0:50:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first Bible 
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.15,0:50:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,printed using movable type.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.85,0:50:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an original page\Nfrom a Gutenberg Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.15,0:50:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,While only some 180 Bibles were made,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.26,0:50:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,his invention sparked a printing revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.23,0:50:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just 20 years later,\NAnton Koberger was printing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.83,0:50:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 1,000 Bibles per run,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.77,0:51:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,making it the first mass-produced Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.44,0:51:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,On display is an original copy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.38,0:51:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the second edition
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.38,0:51:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of Koberger’s Latin Bible from 1477.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.88,0:51:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in the early 1500’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.95,0:51:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible scholars took a renewed interest
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.59,0:51:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the original Bible languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.19,0:51:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For the very first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.46,0:51:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the original-language Hebrew\Nand Greek Scriptures were printed together.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.80,0:51:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Complutensian Polyglot,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.44,0:51:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,printed between 1514 and 1517.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.14,0:51:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A polyglot is a book
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.98,0:51:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with text in several languages\Narranged in columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.71,0:51:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Complutensian Polyglot,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.38,0:51:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible text appears in Latin,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.98,0:51:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrew, Aramaic, and Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.79,0:51:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Comparing the Hebrew text with the Latin,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.29,0:51:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,scholars could see where God’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.63,0:51:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,had been replaced\Nin the Latin Vulgate with “LORD.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.13,0:52:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But would seeing the divine name\Nin the original Hebrew text
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.24,0:52:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,lead Bible translators to restore
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.97,0:52:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s name in their translations?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.51,0:52:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, some did!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.24,0:52:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1551,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.85,0:52:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sebastian Castellio published
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.32,0:52:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,his fresh Latin translation of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.52,0:52:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He appears to be the first
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.82,0:52:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to use God’s name consistently
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.02,0:52:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in a Latin translation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.69,0:52:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.69,0:52:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Translations into other languages
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.53,0:52:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,were also using God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.53,0:52:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1530, William Tyndale
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.20,0:52:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,published his English translation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.54,0:52:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of Genesis through Deuteronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.61,0:52:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.61,0:52:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that the divine name appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.61,0:52:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in any English Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.85,0:52:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The popular Reina-Valera Spanish Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.65,0:52:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was published in 1602.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.35,0:52:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It contains the divine name
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.49,0:52:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.46,0:53:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a rare original first edition
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.23,0:53:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the English King James Version
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.56,0:53:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Bible, published in 1611.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.20,0:53:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It uses the name Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.24,0:53:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in just four passages.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.31,0:53:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the King James Version became
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.64,0:53:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the most widely printed book in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.41,0:53:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Some 200 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.68,0:53:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Benjamin Boothroyd,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.68,0:53:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a minister and Hebrew scholar,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.02,0:53:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,set out to revise the King James Version.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.26,0:53:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,His 1817 translation
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.32,0:53:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was the first English Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.36,0:53:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to use the divine name throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.73,0:53:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.83,0:53:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, church missionaries
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.27,0:53:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were taking the Bible to new lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.60,0:53:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But without the divine name,\Npeople couldn’t distinguish
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.91,0:53:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of the Bible\Nfrom their own false gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.94,0:53:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So Bible translations
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.38,0:53:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in many languages of Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.72,0:53:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Africa, the Pacific islands,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.05,0:54:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Americas included God’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.09,0:54:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chinese Delegate’s Version from 1854
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.53,0:54:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is an example of a missionary Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.30,0:54:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that uses God’s name throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.53,0:54:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.87,0:54:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, there was
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.87,0:54:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,one more place where God’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.47,0:54:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,was not yet restored
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.14,0:54:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Christian Greek Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.68,0:54:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Nuremberg Polyglot,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.61,0:54:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,published by Elias Hutter in 1599.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.65,0:54:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It contains the Christian Greek Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.39,0:54:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in 12 languages, including Hebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.26,0:54:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Here,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.76,0:54:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,John’s Gospel\Nquotes Psalm 118:26:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.56,0:54:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Blessed is the one who comes\Nin Jehovah’s name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.10,0:54:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In his Hebrew translation of the Gospel,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.97,0:54:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hutter preserved the divine name\Nin the quotation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.27,0:54:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from Psalms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.84,0:54:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He did this in many other places\Nin the Greek Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.01,0:55:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Translators had a precedent
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.72,0:55:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to use God’s name\Nin the Christian Greek Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.92,0:55:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where the name appeared\Nin verses quoted from the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.99,0:55:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the 1864 sixth edition
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.83,0:55:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,New Testament translation
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.03,0:55:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by Herman Heinfetter.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.33,0:55:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s likely the first published
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.70,0:55:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,English Bible to use God’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.30,0:55:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in more than 100 places
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.84,0:55:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Christian Greek Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.21,0:55:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The New World Translation\Nof the Holy Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.78,0:55:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,was first published between 1950 and 1960.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.28,0:55:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Its translators benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.85,0:55:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from the scholarly work of those before them
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.99,0:55:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who had chosen to preserve God’s name\Nin their Bible translations.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.96,0:55:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.30,0:55:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is available in whole or in part
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.33,0:55:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in over 170 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.57,0:55:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s name, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.57,0:56:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,belongs in the Holy Scriptures he inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.84,0:56:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This gallery holds just a small part
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.35,0:56:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the overwhelming evidence to this fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.32,0:56:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible is a precious gift from God,\Nteaching us
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.62,0:56:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about his works, his qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.76,0:56:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and his loving purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.76,0:56:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.76,0:56:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He invites each of us to read it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.40,0:56:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to draw close to him, and to know him
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.74,0:56:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by his most holy name, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.74,0:56:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our program has focused
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.78,0:56:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on “perfecting holiness in God’s fear.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.48,0:56:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Perfecting holiness” may sound out of reach,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.85,0:56:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but remember, it’s a continuous process.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.52,0:56:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw this with those young men in Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.33,0:56:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who left behind\Ntheir violent and immoral ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.23,0:56:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Jane, Yusuke, and Yutaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.87,0:57:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw experienced Christians who found ways 
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.40,0:57:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to grow as spiritual people.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.17,0:57:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned how to make\Nour speech more upbuilding
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.91,0:57:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by examining our motives and associations.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.15,0:57:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Petter Heinrichs’ experience demonstrates
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.25,0:57:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s possible\Nto return to Jehovah with His help.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.05,0:57:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, our music video reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.82,0:57:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that despite the unique pressures
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.89,0:57:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,our young people face,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.56,0:57:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re winning the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.60,0:57:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We close with a visit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.90,0:57:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to our brothers and sisters in Puerto Rico.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.30,0:57:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Secluded beaches, lush valleys, mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.31,0:57:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—this beautiful island is home
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.64,0:57:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to more than 3 million inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.08,0:57:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and nearly 24,000 Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.08,0:57:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But its location in the Caribbean\Nputs Puerto Rico in the path
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.52,0:57:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of tropical storms and hurricanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.42,0:58:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most powerful ever,\NHurricane Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.46,0:58:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,struck two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.50,0:58:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lives were lost, and homes were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.03,0:58:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire island\Nlost electricity for months.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.67,0:58:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To help with relief efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.80,0:58:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of brothers and sisters\Nfrom Puerto Rico
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.67,0:58:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and from across the United States\Nbranch territory volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.78,0:58:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They repaired and rebuilt
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.81,0:58:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,106 Kingdom Halls, 2 Assembly Halls,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.15,0:58:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and more than 800 homes of our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.12,0:58:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Barahona Congregation,\Nlocated in the middle of the island,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.33,0:58:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was enjoying their circuit overseer visit\Nwhen the hurricane hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.46,0:58:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The body of elders and the circuit overseer
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.37,0:58:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately organized and reached out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.94,0:58:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to everyone in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.07,0:58:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the devastation,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.41,0:58:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Sunday meeting took place as scheduled.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.38,0:58:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, despite dealing\Nwith challenging conditions for many months,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.48,0:59:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregation\Ndidn’t cancel a single meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.39,0:59:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Within a few days of Hurricane Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.12,0:59:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the organized preaching work resumed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.66,0:59:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and our brothers were back in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.16,0:59:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The response has been encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.70,0:59:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifty Bible studies are now being conducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.74,0:59:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The 117 publishers\Nin the Barahona Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.38,0:59:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,send you\Ntheir warm Christian love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.75,0:59:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.45,0:59:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
